properties.Name: Allegan
properties.Label: Allegan County
properties.funFact: Allegan County comprises the Holland, Michigan Micropolitan Statistical Area. The county has long been a regional tourist draw, particularly the Tulip Time Festival in Holland and the area along Lake Michigan. The Lake Michigan shoreline has long been a popular place for vacation homes. Allegan County contains Saugatuck Dunes State Park with trails through scenic dunes and a swimming beach on Lake Michigan.

properties.Name: Alpena
properties.Label: Alpena County
properties.funFact: Alpena is frequently cited as one of the driest locations in Michigan and the Eastern United States, with an average annual rainfall of approximately 28.8 inches. While not always the absolute driest in the state, it often experiences very low precipitation levels, such as May 2023, when it recorded only 0.96 inches of rain.

properties.Name: Barry
properties.Label: Barry County
properties.funFact: Barry County is one of ten Michigan counties named after members of President Andrew Jacksonâ€™s cabinet, specifically William T. Barry, the U.S. Postmaster General.

properties.Name: Berrien
properties.Label: Berrien County
properties.funFact: Berrien County is located at the southwest corner of the state's Lower Peninsula, located on the shore of Lake Michigan and sharing a land border with Indiana. Berrien contains Whirlpool Corporation, an American multinational manufacturer and marketer of home appliances, headquartered in Benton Charter Township.

properties.Name: Chippewa
properties.Label: Chippewa County
properties.funFact: With shorelines on Lake Huron and Lake Superior, Chippewa County is one of two U.S. counties to contain shorelines on two Great Lakes. Chippewa County is home of the historic Soo Locks in Sault Ste. Marie, and Whitefish point in Paradise, Michigan.

properties.Name: Hillsdale
properties.Label: Hillsdale County
properties.funFact: Hillsdale County, Michigan, is best known for the nationally recognized, conservative Hillsdale College, its scenic, hilly geography, and its significant Amish population. Hillsdale County has the highest concentration of Amish residents in Michigan.

properties.Name: Ingham
properties.Label: Ingham County
properties.funFact: Ingham County is the County that includes Lansing, Michigan. Lansing is the only state capital in the United States located in a county of which it is not also the seat of government. Ingham county is home to Michigan State University, Auto-Owners Insurance Group, and Jackson National Life Insurance Company. Jackson is a leading U.S. financial services provider and a top-tier annuity provider, ranking 7th among the largest U.S. life insurance companies by total statutory assets.

properties.Name: Jackson
properties.Label: Jackson County
properties.funFact: Jackson County is named for U.S. President Andrew Jackson and considered to be one of Michigan's "Cabinet counties". Jackson County is home to the Michigan Whitetail Hall of Fame, and CMS Energy, a public utility that provides electricity and natural gas to more than 6 million of Michigan's 10 million residents.

properties.Name: Kalamazoo
properties.Label: Kalamazoo County
properties.funFact: Stryker Corporation is an American multinational medical technologies corporation based in Kalamazoo, Michigan. The company is ranked 195th on the Fortune 500[3] and 331st on the Forbes Global 2000.

properties.Name: Kent
properties.Label: Kent County
properties.funFact: Kent County, Michigan, is renowned as a top agricultural hub, with "The Fruit Ridge" area producing nearly 80% of the state's apples, making it a major U.S. apple powerhouse. It is also the second-fastest growing county in Michigan, featuring the state's second-largest city, Grand Rapids. Kent County also conatins Forest Hills, an unincorporated community and the largest census-designated place in America, in terms of both land and population.

properties.Name: Lapeer
properties.Label: Lapeer County
properties.funFact: Lapeer County was part of New France from 1534. In 1763 England took possession of all French territory in North America east of the Mississippi River after winning the Seven Years' War. Lapeer  county features 24 properties on the National Register of Historic Places, including 15 historic houses and four districts. In 2012, a $337 million Powerball ticketâ€”the fourth-largest at the timeâ€”was sold at a Sunoco station in Lapeer.

properties.Name: Macomb
properties.Label: Macomb County
properties.funFact: Macomb County is part of the Detroit metropolitan area. As of the 2020 census, the county had a population of 881,217, making it the third-most populous county in the state. Singer and rapper Kid Rock was known as Robert Ritchie in 1971 in Romeo, Michigan.

properties.Name: Marquette
properties.Label: Marquette County
properties.funFact: Marquette County is renowned as the "Queen City of the North" on Lake Superior, celebrated for its rich iron mining history, rugged, scenic beauty, and premier four-season outdoor recreation. Marquette is the largest county in Michigan by land area, covering approximately 1,821 square miles. The county is named for Father Marquette, a Jesuit missionary. Northern Michigan University,established in 1899, is a four-year university in Marquette.

properties.Name: Mason
properties.Label: Mason County
properties.funFact: Mason County, Michigan, is highly notable as a premier Lake Michigan tourist destination anchored by Ludington, featuring the expansive Ludington State Park, top-tier charter fishing, and historic car ferries.

properties.Name: Oakland
properties.Label: Oakland County
properties.funFact: Oakland County is a principal county of the Detroit metropolitan area, containing the bulk of Detroit's northern suburbs. In 2010, Oakland County was among the ten wealthiest counties in the United States to have over one million residents. Oakland is home to many companies, inclduing Penske Corporation, Inc. in  Bloomfield Township. It is also home to Oakland University

properties.Name: Washtenaw
properties.Label: Washtenaw County
properties.funFact: Domino's Pizza, Inc. is headqaurted in Ann Arbor Township.
